  for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
    fmt.Println(fibonacci(i)) 
  }
}
```

This implements the Fibonacci sequence recursively. An iterative implementation would be:

```go 
func fibonacci(n int) int {
  a, b := 0, 1
  for i := 0; i < n; i++ {
    a, b = b, a+b 
  }
  return a
}
```

The iterative approach is generally preferred over recursive for Fibonacci as it is more efficient for larger inputs.

